p. 54 (HAVE THE PAGE)
=====

(1)
"Since 1978, Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping has looked to the West as a source of
technology and funds while trying to SCREEN OUT Western BELIEFS.   ....
.......
Is it possible to SEPARATE THE FACTS about modernization---industrialism, 
technology, economic diversity---from the values and ATTITUDES that make such
things possible in the first place?"


(2)
"Lastly, it [a modern society] achieves innovation through a CLASH OF IDEAS."


(3) Note also the notion of (?) a belief existing independently of individuals
in:
" The reason is the perpetuation of the Middle Kingdom myth, the AGE-OLD BELIEF
that China is superior to other nations."

